@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Licence conditions";
}

<div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    @await Html.PartialAsync("_PreApplicationGuidanceContents")
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    
    <p class="govuk-body">
        The conditions and requirements of a felling licence depend on the type of tree felling and restocking operation you plan to carry out.
    </p>
    
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-m">Restocking requirements</h1>
    <p class="govuk-body">
        Felling licences usually require an area to be restocked. This means you’ll need to replant trees or allow natural regeneration to maintain woodland cover after felling.
        This helps support forest sustainability and meet legal requirements
    </p>
    
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-m">When restocking is required</h1>
    <p class="govuk-body">
        Restocking is typically required for all felling licences, except for thinning-only tree felling licences.
        These are usually unconditional and do not require restocking.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">
        However, if thinning is combined with other felling operations, conditional licences will require restocking for those other operations.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">
        <a class="govuk-link" asp-action="FellingAndRestockingDefinitions">Learn more about felling and restocking types.</a>
    </p>
    
